    "text": "Erdős Problem #84: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. The cycle set of a graph $G$ on $n$ vertices is a set $A\\subseteq \\{3,\\ldots,n\\}$ such that there is a cycle in $G$ of length $\\ell$ if and only if $\\ell \\in A$. Let $f(n)$ count the number of possible such $A$.\n\nProve that $f(n)=o(2^n)$.\n\nProve that $f(n)/2^{n/2}\\to \\infty$. Prize: no. Tags: cycles, graph theory.",
